included.description: The web development certificate courses focus on creating end-to-end solutions including database/data storage, server-side programming, cross-browser and cross-device rendering, and interactivity. They teach web development best practices and standards, search engine optimization, and creating mobile-ready sites.

Take a holistic approach to designing and building websites. Build a web page as the first exercise in class and we progressively build more feature rich pages and sites as the class progresses. This course is not software specific; it can be completed with just a text editor. The instructor will use Dreamweaver in code view for most of the course. Photoshop will be used to prepare images but the principles behind the image creation will be stressed and the principles will carry over into any program used to process images.

The MSI is a professional degree which prepares students for emerging careers that meet the rapidly growing information-management needs of an increasingly interconnected world. As businesses and society grapple with the challenges and opportunities of the digital age, information professionals play a crucial role in analyzing, systematizing, and evaluating the massive resources generated by the digital revolution. At Michigan, we train students to be leaders and agents of change in a field that is evolving at unprecedented speed.

included.summary:
I am a digital psychologist who blends expertise in psychology with understanding of human-computer interaction and web development to craft better user experiences.

My expertise in these fields comes from a masters degree in Human-Computer Interaction from the University of Michigan School of Information, a second masters degree in Social and Cultural Psychology from the London School of Economics where my dissertation focused on how people communicate and behave in digital spaces and uncovered usability issues in video games, and a web development and design certificate from the University of Wisconsin, Milwaukee. 

Always looking for new connections in the UX field!
